	Gibson split    
	 Los Angeles, April 13 (AP): Court records show Mel Gibsons wife has filed for divorce after 28 years of marriage.      
	 Gibson filed the petition in Los Angeles, citing irreconcilable differences. The petition does not give any details about the split. Robyn Gibson is seeking jewellery and some other property, and has suggested joint custody for their 9-year-old son.      
	The records show that the couple were married in June 1980.     
	Top music    
	 London (Reuters): Scottish singer-songwriter Calvin Harris shot straight to the top of the UK singles chart on Sunday with Im not alone, dislodging US glam diva Lady Gaga, the Official Charts Company said. It is another success for the 25-year-old who collaborated with British rapper Dizzee Rascal on Dance Wiv Me. Lady Gagas Poker Face slipped to number two.
                                                                                                                                                                       
